('optional-first-game-jam-prototype', 'developer-tooling-for-games', 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Optional First Game Jam Prototype', 'Optional practice project: Build a tiny game jam style prototype in 48 hours or less using placeholder assets.', 16, 'choice', 4, 'beginner', '{"whatToBuild":"Build a tiny game jam style prototype in 48 hours or less using placeholder assets.","buildSteps":["Define the First Game Jam Prototype scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: gameplay loop.","Define the player goal, core loop, controls, win/loss condition, and feedback signals.","Build the smallest playable version of the mechanic or scene before adding polish.","Add feedback, balancing values, and one intentional constraint or failure case.","Collect playtest notes or screenshots that show how the mechanic behaves.","Document how to run or review the First Game Jam Prototype deliverable, including inputs, expected outputs, and known limitations."],"source":"roadmap.sh/game-developer","nodeKey":"optional-first-game-jam-prototype"}'::jsonb, false, true, '["Apply Game Development Foundations through a focused First Game Jam Prototype artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a playable First Game Jam Prototype with test notes is available for review.","The First Game Jam Prototype scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
('foundation-readiness-check', 'developer-tooling-for-games', 'checkpoint', 'assessment', NULL, NULL, 'Foundation Readiness Check', 'Review checkpoint for Developer Tooling for Games. The learner consolidates evidence from Git Workflow for Game Projects, Git LFS for Binary Assets, GitHub Issues and Project Boards, File Organization and Naming Conventions, identifies unresolved prerequisite gaps, and decides whether to continue, review selected topics, or complete extra practice before the next roadmap segment.', 17, 'checkpoint', 2, 'beginner', '{"reviewFocus":"Review checkpoint for Developer Tooling for Games. The learner consolidates evidence from Git Workflow for Game Projects, Git LFS for Binary Assets, GitHub Issues and Project Boards, File Organization and Naming Conventions, identifies unresolved prerequisite gaps, and decides whether to continue, review selected topics, or complete extra practice before the next roadmap segment.","reviewCriteria":["List the roadmap items reviewed for this checkpoint.","Provide one evidence artifact such as notes, a diagram, a lab result, code, queries, screenshots, or a project review.","Record at least two gaps, risks, or follow-up actions, or explicitly state that no critical gaps were found.","Use the result to choose one next step: continue, review selected topics, or complete extra practice."],"source":"roadmap.sh/game-developer"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Summarize the main concepts and decisions from Developer Tooling for Games in practical game development terms.", "Identify prerequisite gaps, unclear topics, or risks that should be reviewed before moving forward.", "Create a short evidence artifact that links completed roadmap items to what was learned."]'::jsonb, '["List the roadmap items reviewed for this checkpoint.", "Provide one evidence artifact such as notes, a diagram, a lab result, code, queries, screenshots, or a project review.", "Record at least two gaps, risks, or follow-up actions, or explicitly state that no critical gaps were found.", "Use the result to choose one next step: continue, review selected topics, or complete extra practice."]'::jsonb),
