('required-online-feature-project', 'game-backend-services', 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Required Online Feature Project', 'Milestone project: Build an online feature demo with login or anonymous identity, leaderboard or cloud save, and one multiplayer or backend service integration.', 196, 'choice', 7, 'advanced', '{"whatToBuild":"Build an online feature demo with login or anonymous identity, leaderboard or cloud save, and one multiplayer or backend service integration.","buildSteps":["Define the Online Feature Project scenario, target user or reviewer, and the specific Game Backend Services concepts it will demonstrate.","Define the player goal, core loop, controls, win/loss condition, and feedback signals.","Build the smallest playable version of the mechanic or scene before adding polish.","Add feedback, balancing values, and one intentional constraint or failure case.","Collect playtest notes or screenshots that show how the mechanic behaves.","Keep the scope focused enough to complete, review, and explain the a playable Online Feature Project prototype or gameplay slice with test notes.","Document how to run or review the Online Feature Project deliverable, including inputs, expected outputs, and known limitations."],"source":"roadmap.sh/game-developer","nodeKey":"required-online-feature-project"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Apply Multiplayer, Backend, and Online Services through a focused Online Feature Project artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a playable Online Feature Project prototype or gameplay slice with test notes is available for review.","The Online Feature Project scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
