('required-optimized-release-candidate', 'build-and-release-workflow', 'project', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Required Optimized Release Candidate', 'Milestone project: Create a release candidate build with profiling notes, QA checklist, crash reporting or logs, and platform-ready export settings.', 221, 'choice', 6, 'intermediate', '{"whatToBuild":"Create a release candidate build with profiling notes, QA checklist, crash reporting or logs, and platform-ready export settings.","buildSteps":["Define the Optimized Release Candidate scenario and list the specific items to demonstrate: logs.","Define the player goal, core loop, controls, win/loss condition, and feedback signals.","Build the smallest playable version of the mechanic or scene before adding polish.","Add feedback, balancing values, and one intentional constraint or failure case.","Collect playtest notes or screenshots that show how the mechanic behaves.","Keep the scope focused enough to complete, review, and explain the a playable Optimized Release Candidate prototype or gameplay slice with test notes.","Document how to run or review the Optimized Release Candidate deliverable, including inputs, expected outputs, and known limitations."],"source":"roadmap.sh/game-developer","nodeKey":"required-optimized-release-candidate"}'::jsonb, true, true, '["Apply Testing, Optimization, Build, and Release through a focused Optimized Release Candidate artifact.","Explain the main design, data, tooling, workflow, or review decisions behind the project.","Validate the result with evidence that another person can inspect.","Document assumptions, limitations, and a concrete follow-up improvement."]'::jsonb, '["The a playable Optimized Release Candidate prototype or gameplay slice with test notes is available for review.","The Optimized Release Candidate scope, setup path, input data or scenario, and expected output are documented.","The main workflow runs or can be inspected through a notebook, repository, dashboard, prototype, report, configuration, or case study.","Validation evidence is included and directly relates to the project brief.","The notes identify trade-offs, limitations, and one next improvement without claiming mastery or job readiness."]'::jsonb),
